A: You should use println() instead of write() to write a string and a newline character.
printWriter.println("1");
printWriter.println("2");
printWriter.println("3");
printWriter.flush();

The println() method automatically appends a newline character to the end of the string, and flush() is used to ensure that the data is sent immediately.

